parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective headlight design can cause poor visibility while driving at night, leading to hazardous conditions and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: inability to see obstacles or road ahead

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control deactivation switch can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential fires.
symptoms: the vehicle takes off on its own
the cruise control fails to disengage
the cruise control cable is not connected at the factory.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the wiring harness switch can cause internal leaks, overheating, smoking, and burning, leading to electrical fires and damage to the vehicle's interior.
symptoms: The wiring harness switch leaks internally
causing damage to the vehicle's interior.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The weak headlights can cause poor visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights provide very little lighting for the road
making it difficult to read street signs
and requiring high beams to be used even on well-lit roads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause transmission failure, leading to loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially at high speeds.
A bent drive shaft can cause loss of control, vibration, and noise, increasing the risk of accidents.
The sudden and unexpected shift of the transmission into reverse or drive can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission shifts unexpectedly into reverse or drive
